#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:0.3"
msgid "Pārājikakaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Expulsion"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:0.4"
msgid "Catut­tha­pā­rāji­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "4. The fourth training rule"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pj4.1.1, pts-vp-en1.151, pts-vp-pli3.87, ms1V_534
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭā­gāra­sālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā sandiṭṭhā sambhattā bhikkhū vaggumudāya nadiyā tīre vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu."
msgstr "At that time a number of monks who were friends had entered the rains residence on the banks of the river Vaggumudā."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vajjī dubbhikkhā hoti dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā,"
msgstr "Just then Vajjī was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.4"
msgid "na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "and it was not easy to get by on almsfood."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.5"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“etarahi kho vajjī dubbhikkhā dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "The monks considered the difficult circumstances, and they thought, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.6"
msgid "Kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vaseyyāma,"
msgstr "“How can we remain united and in harmony, have a comfortable rains,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.7"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilameyyāmā”ti?"
msgstr "and get almsfood without problems?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_535
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.8"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.9"
msgid "“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhema,"
msgstr "“We could work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.10"
msgid "evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.11"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.12"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_536
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.13"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.14"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena."
msgstr "“There’s no need to work for the lay people."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.152
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.15"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ harāma,"
msgstr "Let’s instead take messages for them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.16"
msgid "evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.17"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.18"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_537
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.19"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.20"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena."
msgstr "“There’s no need to work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.21"
msgid "Kiṃ gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ haṭena."
msgstr "nor to take messages for them."

#. VAR: bhāsissāma → bhāsāma (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.22"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissāma—"
msgstr "Let’s instead praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.23"
msgid "‘asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "‘Such a monk has the first absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.24"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu dutiyassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the second absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.25"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu tatiyassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the third,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.26"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu catutthassa jhānassa lābhī,"
msgstr "such a monk the fourth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.27"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu sotāpanno,"
msgstr "such a monk is a stream-enterer,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.28"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu sakadāgāmī,"
msgstr "such a monk a once-returner,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.29"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu anāgāmī,"
msgstr "such a non-returner,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.30"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu arahā,"
msgstr "such a perfected one;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.31"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu tevijjo,"
msgstr "such a monk has the three true insights,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.32"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño’ti."
msgstr "and such the six direct knowledges.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.33"
msgid "Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "Then they’ll give to us."

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.88
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.34"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma,"
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.35"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "and have no problems getting almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.36"
msgid "“Esoyeva kho, āvuso, seyyo yo amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito”ti."
msgstr "Indeed, this is the better way, that we praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_538
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.37"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsiṃsu—"
msgstr "Then those monks praised one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.38"
msgid "“asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī … pe …"
msgstr "“Such a monk has the first absorption …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.39"
msgid "asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño”ti."
msgstr "such a monk has the six direct knowledges.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.40"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā—"
msgstr "And those people thought,"

#. VAR: yesaṃ no → vata no (c1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.41"
msgid "“lābhā vata no, suladdhaṃ vata no, yesaṃ no evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā;"
msgstr "“We’re fortunate that such monks have come to us for the rains residence."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.153
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.42"
msgid "na vata no ito pubbe evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā yathayime bhikkhū sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā”ti,"
msgstr "Such monks as these, who are virtuous and of good character, have never before entered the rains residence with us.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.43"
msgid "te na tādisāni bhojanāni attanā paribhuñjanti mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakam­ma­ka­ra­porisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñāti­sālo­hi­tā­naṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr "And they gave such food and drink to those monks that they did not even eat and drink themselves, or give to their parents, to their wives and children, to their slaves, servants, and workers, to their friends and companions, or to their relatives."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.44"
msgid "Te na tādisāni khādanīyāni sāyanīyāni pānāni attanā khādanti sāyanti pivanti mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakam­ma­ka­ra­porisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñāti­sālo­hi­tā­naṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.1.45"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vaṇṇavā ahesuṃ pīṇindriyā pasan­na­mukha­vaṇṇā vippa­sanna­chavi­vaṇṇā."
msgstr "In this way those monks were handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-pj4.1.2, ms1V_539
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.1"
msgid "Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ vassaṃ­vuṭṭhā­naṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "Now it was the custom for monks who had finished keeping the rains residence to go to see the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaraṃ ādāya yena vesālī tena pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr "So when the rainy-season residence was completed and the three months had elapsed, those monks put their dwellings in order, took their bowls and robes, and departed for Vesālī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.3"
msgid "Anupubbena yena vesālī mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā yena bhagavā tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "When they eventually arrived at Vesālī, they went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood. There they approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_540, pts-vp-en1.154
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū kisā honti lūkhā dubbaṇṇā uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jātā dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gattā;"
msgstr "At that time the monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in that region were thin, haggard, and pale, their veins protruding all over their limbs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.6"
msgid "vaggu­mudā­tīriyā pana bhikkhū vaṇṇavā honti pīṇindriyā pasan­na­mukha­vaṇṇā vippa­sanna­chavi­vaṇṇā."
msgstr "But the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā were handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.7"
msgid "Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ āgantukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodituṃ."
msgstr "It is the custom for Buddhas to greet newly arrived monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "and so the Master said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.9"
msgid "“kacci, bhikkhave, khamanīyaṃ kacci yāpanīyaṃ kacci samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha,"
msgstr "“I hope you’re keeping well, monks, I hope you’re comfortable; I hope you spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.10"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr "and that you had no trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.11"
msgid "“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā."
msgstr "“We’re keeping well, Master, we’re comfortable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.12"
msgid "Samaggā ca mayaṃ, bhante, sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasimhā,"
msgstr "we spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.13"
msgid "na ca piṇḍakena kilamimhā”ti."
msgstr "and we had no trouble getting almsfood.”"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.89
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.14"
msgid "Jānantāpi tathāgatā pucchanti, jānantāpi na pucchanti … pe …"
msgstr "Buddhas sometimes ask knowing, and knowing sometimes do not ask; they ask knowing the right time to ask, and they ask knowing the right time not to ask. Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, not when it is unbeneficial; in regard to what is unbeneficial, the Buddhas have destroyed the bridge."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.15"
msgid "dvīhākārehi buddhā bhagavanto bhikkhū paṭipucchanti—"
msgstr "Buddhas question the monks for two reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.16"
msgid "“dhammaṃ vā desessāma, sāvakānaṃ vā sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmā”ti."
msgstr "to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_541
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.17"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "And the Master said to those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.18"
msgid "“yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“In what way, monks, did you spend the rains at ease, without having any trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.19"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those monks told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.20"
msgid "“Kacci pana vo, bhikkhave, bhūtan”ti?"
msgstr "“But had you really achieved those superhuman qualities?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.21"
msgid "“Abhūtaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.22"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.155
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.23"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisā, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s unsuitable, foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not fitting for an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.24"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatha."
msgstr "How can you for the sake of your stomachs praise one another’s superhuman qualities to lay people?"

#. VAR: govikantanena → govikattanena (bj, pts1, mr) | govikatthanena (si)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.25"
msgid "Varaṃ tumhehi, moghapurisā, tiṇhena govikantanena kucchi parikanto, na tveva udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttari­manus­sa­dhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito."
msgstr "It would be better for your bellies to be cut open with a sharp butcher’s knife than for you to praise one another’s superhuman qualities to lay people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.26"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.27"
msgid "Tatonidānañhi, moghapurisā, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ,"
msgstr "Because for that reason you might die or experience death-like suffering,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.28"
msgid "na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "but you wouldn’t because of that be reborn in a bad destination."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.29"
msgid "Itonidānañca kho, moghapurisā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "But for *this* reason you might."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.30"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.2.31"
msgid "vigarahitvā dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "After criticizing them and giving a teaching, he addressed the monks:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pj4.1.3, ms1V_542
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, mahācorā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, there are these five great gangsters to be found in the world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa mahācorassa evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "A great gangster thinks like this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.4"
msgid "‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu āhiṇḍissāmi"
msgstr "‘Oh when will I, with a following of a hundred or a thousand men, wander among villages, towns, and royal capitals,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.5"
msgid "hananto ghātento"
msgstr "killing and making others kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.6"
msgid "chindanto chedāpento"
msgstr "destroying and making others destroy,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.7"
msgid "pacanto pācento’ti."
msgstr "tormenting and making others torment?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.8"
msgid "So aparena samayena satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu āhiṇḍati hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento pacanto pācento."
msgstr "Then after some time, he does just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.9"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa pāpabhikkhuno evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "Just so, monks, a bad monk thinks like this:"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.156
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.10"
msgid "‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu cārikaṃ carissāmi sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito gahaṭ­ṭhā­nañ­ceva pabbajitānañca,"
msgstr "‘Oh when will I, with a following of a hundred or a thousand people, go wandering among villages, towns, and royal capitals; be honored, respected, and revered by both lay people and those gone forth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.11"
msgid "lābhī cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­rā­nan’ti."
msgstr "and obtain robe-cloth, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines?’"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.90
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.12"
msgid "So aparena samayena satena vā sahassena vā parivuto gāmani­gama­rāja­dhānīsu cārikaṃ carati sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito gahaṭ­ṭhā­nañ­ceva pabbajitānañca, lābhī cīvara­piṇḍa­pāta­se­nāsa­na­gilā­nappac­caya­bhesaj­ja­parik­khā­rā­naṃ."
msgstr "Then after some time, he does just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. #1"
msgstr "This is the first great gangster to be found in the world."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_543
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.14"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu tathā­gatap­pa­vedi­taṃ dhammavinayaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā attano dahati."
msgstr "Again, a bad monk learns the Teaching and training proclaimed by the Buddha and takes it as his own."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. #2"
msgstr "This is the second great gangster to be found in the world."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_544
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.16"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu suddhaṃ brahmacāriṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carantaṃ amūlakena abrahma­cari­yena anuddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Again, a bad monk groundlessly accuses someone who lives the spiritual life in purity of not abstaining from sexuality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.17"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. #3"
msgstr "This is the third great gangster to be found in the world."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_545
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.18"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco pāpabhikkhu yāni tāni saṃghassa garubhaṇḍāni garu­parik­khā­rāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Again, a bad monk takes valuable goods and equipment belonging to the Order—"

# NOTE: I have rendered _muñja_-reed and _pabbaja_-reed with the single word “reed.” I am not aware that these two types of reed can be distinguished in English.
#. VAR: bibbohanaṃ → bimbohanaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: parasu → pharasu (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.19"
msgid "ārāmo ārāmavatthu vihāro vihāravatthu mañco pīṭhaṃ bhisi bibbohanaṃ lohakumbhī lohabhāṇakaṃ lohavārako lohakaṭāhaṃ vāsi parasu kuṭhārī kudālo nikhādanaṃ valli veḷu muñjaṃ pabbajaṃ tiṇaṃ mattikā dārubhaṇḍaṃ mattikābhaṇḍaṃ,"
msgstr "a monastery, the land of a monastery, a dwelling, the land of a dwelling, a bed, a bench, a mattress, a pillow, a metal pot, a metal jar, a metal bucket, a metal bowl, a machete, a hatchet, an axe, a spade, a chisel, a creeper, bamboo, reed, grass, clay, wooden articles, earthenware articles—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.20"
msgid "tehi gihiṃ saṅgaṇhāti upalāpeti."
msgstr "and uses them to win over and create a following among lay people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho mahācoro santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. #4"
msgstr "This is the fourth great gangster to be found in the world."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-vp-en1.157, ms1V_546
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.22"
msgid "Sadevake, bhikkhave, loke samārake sabrahmake ­sassama­ṇab­rāhma­ṇiyā pajāya sade­va­manus­sāya ayaṃ aggo mahācoro yo asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapati."
msgstr "But in this world with its gods, its lords of death, and its supreme beings, in this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans, this is the greatest gangster: he who untruthfully and groundlessly boasts about a superhuman quality."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.23"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.24"
msgid "Theyyāya vo, bhikkhave, raṭṭhapiṇḍo bhutto”ti. #5"
msgstr "Monks, you’ve eaten the country’s almsfood by theft.”"

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_547
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.25"
msgid "Aññathā santamattānaṃ,"
msgstr "Whoever should declare himself"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.26"
msgid "aññathā yo pavedaye;"
msgstr "to be other than he truly is,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.27"
msgid "Nikacca kitavasseva,"
msgstr "Has eaten this by theft,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.28"
msgid "bhuttaṃ theyyena tassa taṃ."
msgstr "like a cheater who has deceived."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_548
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.29"
msgid "Kāsāvakaṇṭhā bahavo,"
msgstr "Many ocher-necks of bad qualities,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.30"
msgid "pāpadhammā asaññatā;"
msgstr "uncontrolled and wicked—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.31"
msgid "Pāpā pāpehi kammehi,"
msgstr "By their wicked deeds,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.32"
msgid "nirayaṃ te upapajjare."
msgstr "they are reborn in hell."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_549
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.33"
msgid "Seyyo ayoguḷo bhutto,"
msgstr "It is better to eat an iron ball,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.34"
msgid "tatto aggisikhūpamo;"
msgstr "heated, like a burning flame,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.35"
msgid "Yañce bhuñjeyya dussīlo,"
msgstr "Than for the immoral and uncontrolled"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.36"
msgid "raṭṭhapiṇḍaṃ asaññatoti."
msgstr "to eat the country’s alms."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. VAR: bhagavā → bhagavā te (c1)
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_550,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.37"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggu­mudā­tīriye bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya dupposatāya … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā in various ways for being difficult to maintain, difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.38"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "“… And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_551, pts-vp-en1.158
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.39"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu anabhijānaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ attupanāyikaṃ ala­mariya­ñāṇadas­sanaṃ samudācareyya—"
msgstr "‘If a monk falsely claims for himself a superhuman quality, knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.40"
msgid "‘iti jānāmi iti passāmī’ti,"
msgstr "“This I know, this I see,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.41"
msgid "tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā āpanno visuddhāpekkho evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "but after some time—whether questioned or not, but having committed the offense and desiring purification—should say:"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.91
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.42"
msgid "‘ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ jānāmi,"
msgstr "“Not knowing I said that I know,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.43"
msgid "apassaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "not seeing that I see;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.44"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapin’ti,"
msgstr "what I said was empty and false,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.45"
msgid "ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_552
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:1.3.46"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc20, pts-cs-bu-pj4.2, ms1V_553
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte pattasaññino anadhigate adhi­gata­saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino adhimānena aññaṃ byākariṃsu."
msgstr "At one time a number of monks, thinking they had seen what they had not, attained what they had not, achieved what they had not, realized what they had not, declared final knowledge because of overestimation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ aparena samayena rāgāyapi cittaṃ namati dosāyapi cittaṃ namati mohāyapi cittaṃ namati."
msgstr "After some time, their minds inclined to sensual desire, ill-will, and confusion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ ahosi—"
msgstr "They became remorseful, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.4"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ."
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.5"
msgid "Mayañcamha adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte pattasaññino anadhigate adhi­gata­saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino, adhimānena aññaṃ byākarimhā."
msgstr "yet we declared final knowledge because of overestimation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.6"
msgid "Kacci nu kho mayaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpannā”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that we’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.7"
msgid "Te āyasmato ānandassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.8"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "who told the Master."

#. VAR: ānanda → honti te ānanda (bj) | honti yevānanda (s1) | hontiyevānanda (s2, s3)
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.159,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.9"
msgid "“Honti ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū adiṭṭhe diṭṭhasaññino apatte pattasaññino anadhigate adhi­gata­saññino asacchikate ­sacchi­kata­saññino adhimānena aññaṃ byākaronti."
msgstr "He said, “Ānanda, these monks declared final knowledge because of overestimation, thinking they had seen what they had not, attained what they had not, achieved what they had not, realized what they had not,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.10"
msgid "Tañca kho etaṃ abbohārikan”ti."
msgstr "but this is negligible."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_554
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.11"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: attupanāyikaṃ → attūpanāyikaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_555
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.12"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu anabhijānaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ attupanāyikaṃ ala­mariya­ñāṇadas­sanaṃ samudācareyya—"
msgstr "‘If a monk falsely claims for himself a superhuman quality, knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.13"
msgid "‘iti jānāmi iti passāmī’ti,"
msgstr "“This I know, this I see,”"

#. VAR: sama­nug­gāhīya­māno → sama­nug­gāhiya­māno (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: asama­nug­gāhīya­māno → asama­nug­gāhiya­māno (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.14"
msgid "tato aparena samayena sama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā asama­nug­gāhīya­māno vā āpanno visuddhāpekkho evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "but after some time—whether he is questioned or not, but having committed the offense and desiring purification—should say:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.15"
msgid "‘ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ jānāmi,"
msgstr "“Not knowing I said that I know,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.16"
msgid "apassaṃ passāmi."
msgstr "not seeing that I see;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.17"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapin’ti,"
msgstr "what I said was empty and false,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.18"
msgid "aññatra adhimānā,"
msgstr "unless it is due to overestimation,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:2.19"
msgid "ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-pj4.3, ms1V_556,   
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span> <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc24, ms1V_557
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.6"
msgid "Anabhijānanti"
msgstr "Falsely:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.7"
msgid "asantaṃ abhūtaṃ asaṃvijjamānaṃ ajānanto apassanto attani kusalaṃ dhammaṃ—"
msgstr "although a certain wholesome quality is non-existent in himself, not real, not to be found, and he does not see it or know it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.8"
msgid "atthi me kusalo dhammoti."
msgstr "he says, “I have this wholesome quality.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc25, ms1V_558
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.9"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A superhuman quality:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: vimokkho → vimokkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.10"
msgid "jhānaṃ vimokkho samādhi samāpatti ñāṇadassanaṃ maggabhāvanā phala­sacchi­kiriyā kilesappahānaṃ vinīvaraṇatā cittassa suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr "absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in empty dwellings."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc26, ms1V_559
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.11"
msgid "Attupanāyikanti"
msgstr "For himself:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.12"
msgid "te vā kusale dhamme attani upaneti attānaṃ vā tesu kusalesu dhammesu upaneti."
msgstr "either he presents those good qualities as in himself, or he presents himself as among those good qualities."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc27, ms1V_560
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.13"
msgid "Ñāṇanti"
msgstr "Knowledge:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.14"
msgid "tisso vijjā."
msgstr "the three true insights."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.15"
msgid "Dassananti"
msgstr "Vision:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.16"
msgid "yaṃ ñāṇaṃ taṃ dassanaṃ, yaṃ dassanaṃ taṃ ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "knowledge and vision are equivalent."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc28, pts-vp-pli3.92, ms1V_561
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.17"
msgid "Samudācareyyāti"
msgstr "Claims:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.18"
msgid "āroceyya itthiyā vā purisassa vā gahaṭṭhassa vā pabbajitassa vā."
msgstr "announces to a woman or a man, to a lay person or one gone forth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc29, ms1V_562
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.19"
msgid "Iti jānāmi iti passāmīti"
msgstr "This I know, this I see:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.20"
msgid "jānāmahaṃ ete dhamme,"
msgstr "“I know these qualities/"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.160
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.21"
msgid "passāmahaṃ ete dhamme atthi ca ete dhammā mayi,"
msgstr "I see these qualities/these qualities are found in me"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.22"
msgid "ahañca etesu dhammesu sandissāmīti."
msgstr "and I conform to them.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc30, ms1V_563
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.23"
msgid "Tato aparena samayenāti"
msgstr "After some time:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.24"
msgid "yasmiṃ khaṇe samudāciṇṇaṃ hoti taṃ khaṇaṃ taṃ layaṃ taṃ muhuttaṃ vītivatte."
msgstr "the moment, the second, the instant after he has made the claim."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc31, ms1V_564
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.25"
msgid "Sama­nug­gāhīya­mānoti"
msgstr "He is questioned:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.26"
msgid "yaṃ vatthu paṭiññātaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vatthusmiṃ sama­nug­gāhīya­māno—"
msgstr "he is questioned in regard to what he has admitted:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.27"
msgid "“kinte adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "“What did you attain?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.28"
msgid "kinti te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "How did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.29"
msgid "kadā te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "When did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.30"
msgid "kattha te adhigataṃ,"
msgstr "Where did you attain it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.31"
msgid "katame te kilesā pahīnā,"
msgstr "Which defilements did you abandon?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.32"
msgid "katamesaṃ tvaṃ dhammānaṃ lābhī”ti."
msgstr "Which qualities did you gain?”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc32, ms1V_565
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.33"
msgid "Asama­nug­gāhīya­mānoti"
msgstr "Not:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.34"
msgid "na kenaci vuccamāno."
msgstr "he is not spoken to by anyone."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc33, ms1V_566
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.35"
msgid "Āpannoti"
msgstr "Having committed the offense:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.36"
msgid "pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapitvā pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti."
msgstr "having bad desires, overcome by desire, claiming a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, he has committed an offense entailing expulsion."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc34, ms1V_567
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.37"
msgid "Visuddhāpekkhoti"
msgstr "Desiring purification:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.38"
msgid "gihī vā hotukāmo upāsako vā hotukāmo ārāmiko vā hotukāmo sāmaṇero vā hotukāmo."
msgstr "he desires to be a lay person, a lay follower, a monastery worker, or a novice monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc35, ms1V_568
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.39"
msgid "Ajānamevaṃ, āvuso, avacaṃ—jānāmi, apassaṃ passāmīti"
msgstr "Not knowing I said that I know, not seeing that I see:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.40"
msgid "nāhaṃ ete dhamme jānāmi,"
msgstr "“I don’t know these qualities/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.41"
msgid "nāhaṃ ete dhamme passāmi,"
msgstr "I don’t see these qualities/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.42"
msgid "natthi ca ete dhammā mayi,"
msgstr "these qualities aren’t found in me"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.43"
msgid "na cāhaṃ etesu dhammesu sandissāmīti."
msgstr "and I don’t conform to them.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc36, ms1V_569
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.44"
msgid "Tucchaṃ musā vilapinti"
msgstr "What I said was empty and false:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.45"
msgid "tucchakaṃ mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was empty;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.46"
msgid "musā mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was false;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.47"
msgid "abhūtaṃ mayā bhaṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "what I said was unreal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.48"
msgid "ajānantena mayā bhaṇitaṃ."
msgstr "I said it without knowing."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc37, ms1V_570
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.49"
msgid "Aññatra adhimānāti"
msgstr "Unless it is due to overestimation:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.50"
msgid "ṭhapetvā adhimānaṃ."
msgstr "except if it is overestimation."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc38, ms1V_571
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.51"
msgid "Ayampīti"
msgstr "He too:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.52"
msgid "purime upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc39, ms1V_572
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.53"
msgid "Pārājiko hotīti"
msgstr "Is expelled:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.161
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.54"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma tālo mattha­kac­chinno abhabbo puna virūḷhiyā;"
msgstr "just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.55"
msgid "evameva bhikkhu pāpiccho icchāpakato asantaṃ abhūtaṃ uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapitvā assamaṇo hoti asakyaputtiyo."
msgstr "so too a monk with bad desires, overcome by desire, who has claimed a non-existent, unreal superhuman quality, is not an ascetic, not a son of the Sakyan—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.56"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.57"
msgid "“pārājiko hotī”ti."
msgstr "“he is expelled.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc40, ms1V_573
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.58"
msgid "Asaṃvāsoti"
msgstr "Excluded from the community:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.59"
msgid "saṃvāso nāma"
msgstr "Community:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.60"
msgid "ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā—"
msgstr "common procedures, the same recital, the same training—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.61"
msgid "eso saṃvāso nāma."
msgstr "this is called “community.”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.62"
msgid "So tena saddhiṃ natthi."
msgstr "He does not take part in this—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.63"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is called"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:3.64"
msgid "“asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "“excluded from the community.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: sc41, pts-cs-bu-pj4.4.1, ms1V_574
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.1"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A superhuman quality:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.2"
msgid "jhānaṃ vimokkho samādhi samāpatti ñāṇadassanaṃ maggabhāvanā phala­sacchi­kiriyā kilesappahānaṃ vinīvaraṇatā cittassa suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr "absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in empty dwellings."

#. HTML: </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.2a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h4><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc42, ms1V_575
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.3"
msgid "Jhānanti"
msgstr "Absorption:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.4"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the first absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.5"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the second absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ"
msgstr "the third absorption,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ."
msgstr "the fourth absorption."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc43, ms1V_576
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.8"
msgid "Vimokkhoti"
msgstr "Release:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.9"
msgid "suññato vimokkho"
msgstr "emptiness release,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.10"
msgid "animitto vimokkho"
msgstr "signless release,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.11"
msgid "appaṇihito vimokkho."
msgstr "desireless release."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc44, pts-vp-pli3.93, ms1V_577
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.12"
msgid "Samādhīti"
msgstr "Stillness:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.13"
msgid "suññato samādhi"
msgstr "emptiness stillness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.14"
msgid "animitto samādhi"
msgstr "signless stillness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.15"
msgid "appaṇihito samādhi."
msgstr "desireless stillness."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc45, ms1V_578
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.16"
msgid "Samāpattīti"
msgstr "Attainment:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.17"
msgid "suññatā samāpatti"
msgstr "emptiness attainment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.18"
msgid "animittā samāpatti"
msgstr "signless attainment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.19"
msgid "appaṇihitā samāpatti."
msgstr "desireless attainment."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc46, ms1V_579
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.20"
msgid "Ñāṇadassananti"
msgstr "Knowledge and vision:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.21"
msgid "tisso vijjā."
msgstr "the three true insights."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc47, ms1V_580
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.22"
msgid "Maggabhāvanāti"
msgstr "Development of the path:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.23"
msgid "cattāro satipaṭṭhānā,"
msgstr "the four applications of mindfulness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.24"
msgid "cattāro sammappadhānā,"
msgstr "the four right efforts,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.162
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.25"
msgid "cattāro iddhipādā,"
msgstr "the four bases of supernormal power,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.26"
msgid "pañcindriyāni,"
msgstr "the five spiritual faculties,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.27"
msgid "pañca balāni,"
msgstr "the five spiritual powers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.28"
msgid "satta bojjhaṅgā,"
msgstr "the seven factors of awakening,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.29"
msgid "ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr "the noble eightfold path."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc48, ms1V_581
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.30"
msgid "Phala­sacchi­kiriyāti"
msgstr "Realization of the fruits:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.31"
msgid "sotā­patti­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of stream-entry,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.32"
msgid "sakadā­gāmi­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of once-returning,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.33"
msgid "anāgā­mi­phalassa sacchikiriyā,"
msgstr "realization of the fruit of non-returning,"

#. VAR: arahattassa → arahat­ta­phalassa (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.34"
msgid "arahattassa sacchikiriyā."
msgstr "realization of perfection."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc49, ms1V_582
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.35"
msgid "Kilesappahānanti"
msgstr "Abandoning the defilements:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.36"
msgid "rāgassa pahānaṃ"
msgstr "the abandoning of sensual desire,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.37"
msgid "dosassa pahānaṃ"
msgstr "the abandoning of ill-will,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.38"
msgid "mohassa pahānaṃ."
msgstr "the abandoning of confusion."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc50, ms1V_583
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.39"
msgid "Vinīvaraṇatā cittassāti"
msgstr "A mind without hindrances:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.40"
msgid "rāgā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā,"
msgstr "a mind without sensual desire,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.41"
msgid "dosā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā,"
msgstr "a mind without ill-will,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.42"
msgid "mohā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā."
msgstr "a mind without confusion."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc51, ms1V_584
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.43"
msgid "Suññāgāre abhiratīti"
msgstr "Delighting in empty dwellings:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.44"
msgid "paṭhamena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati,"
msgstr "because of the first absorption, there is delight in empty dwellings;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.45"
msgid "dutiyena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati,"
msgstr "because of the second absorption, there is delight in empty dwellings;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.46"
msgid "tatiyena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati,"
msgstr "because of the third absorption, there is delight in empty dwellings;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.1.47"
msgid "catutthena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr "because of the fourth absorption, there is delight in empty dwellings."

#. HTML: </span></p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. HTML: </h4><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First absorption"

#. HTML: </h5><p>
#. REF: sc52, pts-cs-bu-pj4.4.2, ms1V_585
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.1"
msgid "Tīhākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjinti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when three conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.2"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.3"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.4"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti."
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53, ms1V_586
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.5"
msgid "Catūhākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjinti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when four conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.6"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.7"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.163
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.8"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti,"
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

# NOTE: “Of what is true” is not in the Pali, but has been added for clarity.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.9"
msgid "vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his view of what is true."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54, ms1V_587
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.10"
msgid "Pañcahākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjinti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when five conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.11"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.12"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.13"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti,"
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.14"
msgid "vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ vinidhāya khantiṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his view of what is true; he misrepresents his belief of what is true."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc55, ms1V_588
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.15"
msgid "Chahākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjinti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when six conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.16"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.17"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.18"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti,"
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.19"
msgid "vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his view of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.20"
msgid "vinidhāya khantiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his belief of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.21"
msgid "vinidhāya ruciṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his acceptance of what is true."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc56, ms1V_589
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.22"
msgid "Sattahākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjinti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.23"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.24"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.25"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti,"
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.26"
msgid "vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his view of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.27"
msgid "vinidhāya khantiṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his belief of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.28"
msgid "vinidhāya ruciṃ,"
msgstr "he misrepresents his acceptance of what is true;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.2.29"
msgid "vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr "he misrepresents his sentiment of what is true."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc57, pts-cs-bu-pj4.4.3, ms1V_590
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.3.1"
msgid "Tīhākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmīti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying, “I’m attaining the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing expulsion when three conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.3.2"
msgid "pubbevassa hoti musā bhaṇissanti,"
msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.3.3"
msgid "bhaṇantassa hoti musā bhaṇāmīti,"
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.3.4"
msgid "bhaṇitassa hoti musā mayā bhaṇitanti."
msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc58, ms1V_591
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:4.3.5"
msgid "Catūhākārehi paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmīti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
