msgid "Sopi evamāha—“mayhampi, āvuso, āsavā pahīnā”ti."
msgstr "“I’ve abandoned the corruptions.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.3"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.4"
msgid "“āpattiṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āpanno pārājikan”ti. #29"
msgstr "“You’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc203, ms1V_736, pts-vp-pli3.104
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu aññatarassa bhikkhuno uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapati."
msgstr "At one time a monk claimed a superhuman quality to another monk:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.6"
msgid "Sopi evamāha—“mayhampi, āvuso, ete dhammā saṃvijjantī”ti."
msgstr "“I have these qualities.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.7"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.8"
msgid "“āpattiṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āpanno pārājikan”ti. #30"
msgstr "“You’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc204, ms1V_737
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.9"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu aññatarassa bhikkhuno uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ ullapati."
msgstr "At one time a monk claimed a superhuman quality to another monk:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.10"
msgid "Sopi evamāha—“ahampāvuso, tesu dhammesu sandissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I conform to these qualities.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.11"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.12.12"
msgid "“āpattiṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āpanno pārājikan”ti. #31"
msgstr "“You’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc205, pts-cs-bu-pj4.8.13, ms1V_738
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ ñātakā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "At one time the relatives of a certain monk said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.2"
msgid "“ehi, bhante, agāraṃ ajjhāvasā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, live at home.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.3"
msgid "“Abhabbo kho, āvuso, mādiso agāraṃ ajjhāvasitun”ti."
msgstr "“One like me is incapable of living at home.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.4"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.5"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, anul­lapa­nādhip­pāyassā”ti. #32"
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who doesn’t intend to make a claim.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc206, ms1V_739
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.6"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ ñātakā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "At one time the relatives of a certain monk said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.7"
msgid "“ehi, bhante, kāme paribhuñjā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, enjoy sense pleasures.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.8"
msgid "“Āvaṭā me, āvuso, kāmā”ti."
msgstr "“The pleasures of the senses have been rejected by me.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.9"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.180
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.10"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, anul­lapa­nādhip­pāyassā”ti. #33"
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who doesn’t intend to make a claim.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc207, ms1V_740
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.11"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ ñātakā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "At one time the relatives of a certain monk said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.12"
msgid "“abhiramasi, bhante”ti?"
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, enjoy yourself.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.13"
msgid "“Abhirato ahaṃ, āvuso, paramāya abhiratiyā”ti."
msgstr "“I’m enjoying myself with the highest enjoyment.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.14"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "He became remorseful,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.15"
msgid "“Ye kho te bhagavato sāvakā te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr "thinking, “Those who are true disciple of the Master may say that,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.16"
msgid "Ahañcamhi na bhagavato sāvako."
msgstr "but I’m not such a disciple."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.17"
msgid "Kacci nu kho ahaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that I’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.18"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.19"
msgid "“Kiṃcitto tvaṃ, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“What was your intention, monk?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.20"
msgid "“Anul­lapa­nā­dhip­pāyo ahaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I didn’t intend to make a claim, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.13.21"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, anul­lapa­nādhip­pāyassā”ti. #34"
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who doesn’t intend to make a claim.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc208, pts-cs-bu-pj4.8.14, ms1V_741
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū katikaṃ katvā aññatarasmiṃ āvāse vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu—"
msgstr "At one time a number of monks entered the rainy season residence in a certain monastery, making this agreement:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.2"
msgid "“yo imamhā āvāsā paṭhamaṃ pakkamissati taṃ mayaṃ arahāti jānissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Whomever sets out from this monastery first, we’ll know him as a perfected one.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.3"
msgid "Aññataro bhikkhu—"
msgstr "One of the monks thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.4"
msgid "“maṃ arahāti jānantū”ti,"
msgstr "“Let them know me as a perfected one,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.5"
msgid "tamhā āvāsā paṭhamaṃ pakkāmi."
msgstr "and he set out first from that monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.6"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "He became remorseful …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:8.14.7"
msgid "“āpattiṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āpanno pārājikan”ti. #35"
msgstr "“You’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Case details, part 2"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc209, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.1, ms1V_742
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.181
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca lakkhaṇo āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭe pabbate viharanti."
msgstr "while Venerable Lakkhaṇa and Venerable Mahāmoggallāna were staying on Mount Vulture Peak."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ ādāya yenāyasmā lakkhaṇo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "One morning Mahāmoggallāna robed up, took his bowl and robe, approached Lakkhaṇa,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ lakkhaṇaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.5"
msgid "“āyāmāvuso lakkhaṇa, rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Lakkhaṇa, let’s enter Rājagaha for almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmato ­mahā­mog­gallā­nassa paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc210, ms1V_743, pts-vp-pli3.105
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi."
msgstr "As they were descending from Mount Vulture Peak, Mahāmoggallāna smiled at a certain place."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmantaṃ ­mahā­mog­gallā­naṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Lakkhaṇa asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.9"
msgid "“ko nu kho, āvuso moggallāna, hetu ko paccayo sitassa pātukammāyā”ti?"
msgstr "“Why are you smiling?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: etassa pañhassa → paṇhassa byākaraṇāya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.10"
msgid "“Akālo kho, āvuso lakkhaṇa, etassa pañhassa."
msgstr "“This isn’t the right time to reply."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.1.11"
msgid "Bhagavato maṃ santike etaṃ pañhaṃ pucchā”ti."
msgstr "Please ask me in the presence of the Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc211, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.2, ms1V_744
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ca lakkhaṇo āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍa­pāta­paṭik­kantā yena bhagavā tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "Then, after their meal and after returning from almsround, Lakkhaṇa and Mahāmoggallāna approached the Master"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmantaṃ ­mahā­mog­gallā­naṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And Lakkhaṇa said to Mahāmoggallāna:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.4"
msgid "“idhāyasmā mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi."
msgstr "“Just now, as you were descending from Mount Vulture Peak, you smiled at a certain place."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.5"
msgid "Ko nu kho, āvuso moggallāna, hetu ko paccayo sitassa pātukammāyā”ti?"
msgstr "Why was that?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.182
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.6"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ aṭṭhi­ka­saṅ­kha­likaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a skeleton flying through the air."

#. VAR: vituḍenti → vitudanti (bj) | vitudenti vitacchenti virājenti (s1-3) | vitudenti (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā phāsu­ḷanta­rikāhi vituḍenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of it, striking it between the ribs,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.8"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti."
msgstr "while it uttered cries of distress."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi—"
msgstr "And I thought"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.10"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, evarūpopi nāma satto bhavissati."
msgstr "how amazing and astonishing it is that such a being should exist,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.11"
msgid "Evarūpopi nāma yakkho bhavissati."
msgstr "such a spirit,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.12"
msgid "Evarūpopi nāma atta­bhāvap­paṭi­lābho bhavissatī’”ti."
msgstr "such a state of existence.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.13"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.14"
msgid "“uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Mahāmoggallāna is claiming a superhuman ability.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc212, ms1V_745
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.15"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "The Master then said to them:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.16"
msgid "“cakkhubhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti."
msgstr "“There are disciples who have vision"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.17"
msgid "Ñāṇabhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti."
msgstr "and knowledge,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.18"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma sāvako evarūpaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sakkhiṃ vā karissati."
msgstr "and they can see, know, and witness such things."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.19"
msgid "Pubbeva me so, bhikkhave, satto diṭṭho ahosi."
msgstr "I too, monks, have seen that being,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.20"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ na byākāsiṃ."
msgstr "but I didn’t speak about it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.21"
msgid "Ahañcetaṃ byākareyyaṃ pare ca me na saddaheyyuṃ."
msgstr "If I had, others wouldn’t have believed me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.22"
msgid "Ye me na saddaheyyuṃ tesaṃ taṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya."
msgstr "and that would have been for their harm and suffering for long time."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.183
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.23"
msgid "Eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe goghātako ahosi."
msgstr "That being was a cattle-butcher in this very Rājagaha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.24"
msgid "So tassa kammassa vipākena bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni bahūni vassa­sata­sahas­sāni niraye paccitvā tasseva kammassa vipākāvasesena evarūpaṃ atta­bhāvap­paṭi­lābhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr "As a result of his deeds, he was tormented in hell for many years, for many hundreds of years, for many thousands of years, for many hundreds of thousands of years. And now, because of the remaining result of his actions, he’s experiencing such an existence."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.25"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, moggallāno āha."
msgstr "Moggallāna spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.2.26"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, moggallānassā”ti. #36"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Moggallāna.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc213, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.3, ms1V_746
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ maṃsapesiṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a lump of flesh flying through the air."

#. VAR: vitacchenti vibhajjenti → vitacchenti virājenti (bj) | vitudenti vitacchenti virājenti (s1-3) | vitacchenti vibhajenti (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of it, tearing at it and pulling it to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.3"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while it uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.106
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.4"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe goghātako ahosi … pe …. #37"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a cattle-butcher in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc214, ms1V_747
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.5"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ maṃsapiṇḍaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a morsel of flesh flying through the air."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.184
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of it, tearing at it and pulling it to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.7"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while it uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.8"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sākuṇiko ahosi … pe …. #38"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a poultry-butcher in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc215, ms1V_748
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.9"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ nicchaviṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a flayed man flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of him, tearing at him and pulling him to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.11"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while he uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.12"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe orabbhiko ahosi … pe …. #39"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a sheep-butcher in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc216, ms1V_749
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.13"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ asilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man who had body hairs of swords flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.14"
msgid "Tassa te asī uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti."
msgstr "Again and again he was stabbed by those swords,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.15"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while uttering cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.16"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sūkariko ahosi … pe …. #40"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a butcher of pigs in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc217, ms1V_750
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.17"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sattilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man with body hairs of knives flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.18"
msgid "Tassa tā sattiyo uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti."
msgstr "Again and again he was stabbed by those knives,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.19"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while uttering cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.20"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe māgaviko ahosi … pe …. #41"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a deer-hunter in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc218, ms1V_751
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.21"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ usulomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man with body hairs of arrows flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.22"
msgid "Tassa te usū uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti."
msgstr "Again and again he was pierced by those arrows,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.23"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while uttering cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.24"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe kāraṇiko ahosi … pe …. #42"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a torturer in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc219, pts-vp-en1.185, ms1V_752
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.25"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sūcilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man with body hairs of needles flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.26"
msgid "Tassa tā sūciyo uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti."
msgstr "Again and again he was pierced by those needles,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.27"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while uttering cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.28"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sārathiko ahosi … pe …. #43"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a horse trainer in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc220, ms1V_753
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.29"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sūcilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man with body hairs of needles flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.30"
msgid "Tassa tā sūciyo sīse pavisitvā mukhato nikkhamanti;"
msgstr "Those needles pierced his head and came out through his mouth,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.31"
msgid "mukhe pavisitvā urato nikkhamanti;"
msgstr "entered his mouth and came out through his breast,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.32"
msgid "ure pavisitvā udarato nikkhamanti;"
msgstr "entered his breast and came out through his stomach,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.33"
msgid "udare pavisitvā ūrūhi nikkhamanti;"
msgstr "entered his stomach and came out through his thighs,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.34"
msgid "ūrūsu pavisitvā jaṅghāhi nikkhamanti;"
msgstr "entered his thighs and came out through his calves,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.35"
msgid "jaṅghāsu pavisitvā pādehi nikkhamanti."
msgstr "entered his calves and came out through his feet—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.36"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "and he uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.37"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sūcako ahosi … pe …. #44"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a slanderer in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc221, ms1V_754
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.38"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ kumbhaṇḍaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man flying through the air who had testicles like pots."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.39"
msgid "So gacchantopi teva aṇḍe khandhe āropetvā gacchati,"
msgstr "When he walked, he had to lift his testicles on to his shoulder;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.40"
msgid "nisīdantopi tesveva aṇḍesu nisīdati."
msgstr "and when he sat down, he sat on top of his testicles."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.41"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of him, tearing at him and pulling him to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.42"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while he uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.43"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe gāmakūṭo ahosi … pe …. #45"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a corrupt magistrate in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc222, ms1V_755
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.44"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ purisaṃ gūthakūpe sasīsakaṃ nimuggaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man sunk over his head in a pit of dung …”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.186
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.45"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe pāradāriko ahosi … pe …. #46"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was an adulterer in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc223, ms1V_756, pts-vp-pli3.107
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.46"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ purisaṃ gūthakūpe sasīsakaṃ nimuggaṃ ubhohi hatthehi gūthaṃ khādantaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a man sunk over his head in a pit of dung, eating dung with both hands …”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.47"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe duṭṭhabrāhmaṇo ahosi."
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was a wicked brahmin in this very Rājagaha."

#. VAR: doṇiyo → doṇiyā (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.48"
msgid "So kassapassa sammā­sambud­dhassa pāvacane bhikkhusaṃghaṃ bhattena nimantetvā doṇiyo gūthassa pūrāpetvā kālaṃ ārocāpetvā etadavoca—"
msgstr "At the time of Kassapa, the fully Awakened One, he invited the Order of monks to a meal. He filled a trough with dung, announced the time, and said,"

#. VAR: ato → ito (s1-3) | aho (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.49"
msgid "‘ato, bhonto, yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjantu ceva harantu cā’”ti … pe …. #47"
msgstr "‘Sirs, eat as much as you like and take the rest away with you.’ …"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc224, ms1V_757
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.50"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ nicchaviṃ itthiṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a flayed woman flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.51"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of her, tearing at her and pulling her to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.52"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while she uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.53"
msgid "esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe aticārinī ahosi … pe …. #48"
msgstr "“… That woman, monks, was an adulteress in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc225, ms1V_758
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.54"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ duggandhaṃ maṅguliṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a foul-smelling and ugly woman flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.55"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of her, tearing at her and pulling her to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.56"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while she uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.57"
msgid "esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe ikkhaṇikā ahosi … pe …. #49"
msgstr "“… That woman, monks, was a fortune-teller in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc226, ms1V_759
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.58"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ uppakkaṃ okiliniṃ okiriniṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a woman flying through the air who was roasting, sweltering, and sooty."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.59"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of her, tearing at her and pulling her to pieces, while she uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.60"
msgid "esā, bhikkhave, itthī kāliṅgassa rañño aggamahesī ahosi."
msgstr "“… That woman, monks, was the chief queen of the King of Kāliṅga."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.61"
msgid "Sā issāpakatā sapattiṃ aṅgārakaṭāhena okiri … pe …. #50"
msgstr "Because of jealousy, she threw out her rival and poured a pan of burning coals over her. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc227, pts-vp-en1.187, ms1V_760
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.62"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ asīsakaṃ kabandhaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw the headless trunk of a body flying through the air,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.63"
msgid "Tassa ure akkhīni ceva honti mukhañca."
msgstr "with eyes and mouth on its chest."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.64"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti vibhajjenti."
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks were in close pursuit of it, tearing at it and pulling it to pieces,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.65"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "while it uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.66"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe hāriko nāma coraghātako ahosi … pe …. #51"
msgstr "“… That being, monks, was an executioner called Hārika in this very Rājagaha. …”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc228, ms1V_761
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.67"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ bhikkhuṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ."
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a monk flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.68"
msgid "Tassa saṅghāṭipi ādittā sampajjalitā sajotibhūtā, pattopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto, kāya­bandha­nampi ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ, kāyopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto."
msgstr "His outer robe was ablaze and burning, as were his bowl, his belt, and his body."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.69"
msgid "So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …"
msgstr "He uttered cries of distress. …” …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.70"
msgid "eso, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kassapassa sammā­sambud­dhassa pāvacane pāpabhikkhu ahosi … pe …. #52"
msgstr "“… During the time of the Buddha Kassapa’s dispensation, that monk was a bad monk.” …"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc229, ms1V_762
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.71"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ bhikkhuniṃ …"
msgstr "“As I was coming down from Mount Vulture Peak, I saw a nun …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.72"
msgid "addasaṃ sikkhamānaṃ …"
msgstr "I saw a trainee nun …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.73"
msgid "addasaṃ sāmaṇeraṃ …"
msgstr "I saw a novice monk …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.74"
msgid "addasaṃ sāmaṇeriṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ."
msgstr "I saw a novice nun flying through the air."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.75"
msgid "Tassā saṅghāṭipi ādittā sampajjalitā sajotibhūtā, pattopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto, kāya­bandha­nampi ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ, kāyopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto."
msgstr "Her outer robe was ablaze and burning, as were her bowl, her belt, and her body."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.76"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti."
msgstr "She uttered cries of distress."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.77"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi—"
msgstr "And I thought"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.78"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, evarūpopi nāma satto bhavissati."
msgstr "how amazing and astonishing it is that such a being should exist,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.79"
msgid "Evarūpopi nāma yakkho bhavissati."
msgstr "such a spirit,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.80"
msgid "Evarūpopi nāma atta­bhāvap­paṭi­lābho bhavissatī’”ti."
msgstr "such a state of existence.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.81"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.82"
msgid "“uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Moggallāna is claiming a superhuman ability.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc230, ms1V_763
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.83"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "The Master then said to them:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.188, pts-vp-pli3.108
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.84"
msgid "“cakkhubhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti."
msgstr "“There are disciples who possess vision"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.85"
msgid "Ñāṇabhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti."
msgstr "and knowledge,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.86"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma sāvako evarūpaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sakkhiṃ vā karissati."
msgstr "and they can see, know, and witness such things."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.87"
msgid "Pubbeva me sā, bhikkhave, sāmaṇerī diṭṭhā ahosi."
msgstr "I too, monks, have seen this novice nun,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.88"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ na byākāsiṃ."
msgstr "but I didn’t speak about it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.89"
msgid "Ahañcetaṃ byākareyyaṃ pare ca me na saddaheyyuṃ."
msgstr "If I had, others wouldn’t have believed me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.90"
msgid "Ye me na saddaheyyuṃ tesaṃ taṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya."
msgstr "and that would have been for their harm and suffering for a long time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.91"
msgid "Esā, bhikkhave, sāmaṇerī kassapassa sammā­sambud­dhassa pāvacane pāpasāmaṇerī ahosi."
msgstr "During the time of Buddha Kassapa’s dispensation, that novice nun was a bad novice nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.92"
msgid "Sā tassa kammassa vipākena bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni bahūni vassa­sata­sahas­sāni niraye paccitvā tasseva kammassa vipākāvasesena evarūpaṃ atta­bhāvap­paṭi­lābhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti."
msgstr "As a result of her deeds, she was tormented in hell for many years, for many hundreds of years, for many thousands of years, for many hundreds of thousands of years. And now, because of the remaining result of her actions, she’s experiencing such an existence."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.93"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, moggallāno āha."
msgstr "Moggallāna spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.3.94"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, moggallānassā”ti. #53–‍56"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Moggallāna.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc231, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.4, ms1V_764
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.2"
msgid "“yatāyaṃ, āvuso, tapodā sandati so daho acchodako sītodako sātodako setako suppatittho ramaṇīyo pahūta­maccha­kacchapo cakkamattāni ca padumāni pupphantī”ti."
msgstr "“This stream, the Tapodā, flows from a lake with beautiful waters—cool, sweet, and pure—with smooth and pleasant banks, with an abundance of fish and turtles, and with blooming lotuses the size of wheels.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā mahāmoggallāno evaṃ vakkhati—"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Mahāmoggallāna say"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.5"
msgid "‘yatāyaṃ, āvuso, tapodā sandati so daho acchodako sītodako sātodako setako suppatittho ramaṇīyo pahūta­maccha­kacchapo cakkamattāni ca padumāni pupphantī’ti."
msgstr "such a thing?"

#. VAR: kuthitā → kuṭṭhitā (s2, s3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.6"
msgid "Atha ca panāyaṃ tapodā kuthitā sandati."
msgstr "On the contrary, the Tapodā is hot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.7"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna is claiming a superhuman ability.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.8"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.9"
msgid "“Yatāyaṃ, bhikkhave, tapodā sandati so daho acchodako sītodako sātodako setako suppatittho ramaṇīyo pahūta­maccha­kacchapo cakkamattāni ca padumāni pupphanti."
msgstr "“Monks, the Tapodā flows from a lake of beautiful waters—with smooth and pleasant banks, with an abundance of fish and turtles, and with blooming lotuses the size of wheels."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.10"
msgid "Api cāyaṃ, bhikkhave, tapodā dvinnaṃ mahānirayānaṃ antarikāya āgacchati."
msgstr "But the Tapodā runs between the two great hells;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.189
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.11"
msgid "Tenāyaṃ tapodā kuthitā sandati."
msgstr "that’s why it’s hot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.12"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, moggallāno āha."
msgstr "Moggallāna spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.4.13"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, moggallānassā”ti. #57"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Moggallāna.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. VAR: ahosi → hoti (bj, s1-3)
#. REF: sc232, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.5, ms1V_765,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro licchavīhi saddhiṃ saṅgāmento pabhaggo ahosi."
msgstr "At one time King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha was defeated in battle by the Licchavīs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.2"
msgid "Atha rājā pacchā senaṃ saṅkaḍḍhitvā licchavayo parājesi."
msgstr "The King then rallied his army and beat the Licchavīs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.3"
msgid "Saṅgāme ca nandī carati—"
msgstr "People were delighted and the word spread:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.4"
msgid "“raññā licchavī pabhaggā”ti."
msgstr "“The Licchavīs have been defeated by the king!”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.6"
msgid "“rājā, āvuso, licchavīhi pabhaggo”ti."
msgstr "“The King was defeated by the Licchavīs.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.7"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā mahāmoggallāno evaṃ vakkhati—"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Moggallāna say"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.9"
msgid "‘rājā, āvuso, licchavīhi pabhaggo’ti."
msgstr "that the King was defeated by the Licchavīs"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.10"
msgid "Saṅgāme ca nandī carati—"
msgstr "when people are delighted"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.11"
msgid "‘raññā licchavī pabhaggā’ti."
msgstr "and the word is spreading that the Licchavīs have been defeated by the King?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.12"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna is claiming a superhuman ability.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.13"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.109
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.14"
msgid "“Paṭhamaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā licchavīhi pabhaggo."
msgstr "“Monks, first the King was defeated by the Licchavīs,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.15"
msgid "Atha rājā pacchā senaṃ saṅkaḍḍhitvā licchavayo parājesi."
msgstr "but then, after he had rallied his army, the King beat the Licchavīs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.16"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, moggallāno āha."
msgstr "Moggallāna spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.5.17"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, moggallānassā”ti. #58"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Moggallāna.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc233, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.6, ms1V_766
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.2"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sappinikāya nadiyā tīre āneñjaṃ samādhiṃ samāpanno nāgānaṃ ogayha uttarantānaṃ koñcaṃ karontānaṃ saddaṃ assosin”ti."
msgstr "“After attaining an imperturbable stillness on the banks of the river Sappinikā, I heard the noise of elephants plunging in, emerging, and trumpeting.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.190
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āneñjaṃ samādhiṃ samāpanno saddaṃ sossati."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Mahāmoggallāna say such a thing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.5"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "He’s claiming a superhuman ability.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.6"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.7"
msgid "“Attheso, bhikkhave, samādhi so ca kho aparisuddho."
msgstr "“Monks, there is such a stillness, but it’s not wholly purified."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.8"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, moggallāno āha."
msgstr "Moggallāna spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.6.9"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, moggallānassā”ti. #59"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Moggallāna.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc234, pts-cs-bu-pj4.9.7, ms1V_767
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sobhito bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Venerable Sobhita said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.2"
msgid "“ahaṃ, āvuso, pañca kappasatāni anussarāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I can recall five hundred eons.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā sobhito evaṃ vakkhati—"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Sobhita say"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ, āvuso, pañca kappasatāni anussarāmī’ti."
msgstr "that he can recall five hundred eons?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.6"
msgid "Uttari­manus­sa­dhammaṃ āyasmā sobhito ullapatī”ti."
msgstr "He’s claiming a superhuman ability.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.8"
msgid "“Atthesā, bhikkhave, sobhitassa."
msgstr "“Monks, Sobhita has this ability,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.9"
msgid "Sā ca kho ekāyeva jāti."
msgstr "and that was just one birth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.10"
msgid "Saccaṃ, bhikkhave, sobhito āha."
msgstr "Sobhita spoke truthfully."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.11"
msgid "Anāpatti, bhikkhave, sobhitassā”ti. #60"
msgstr "There’s no offense for Sobhita.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc235, ms1V_768
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.12"
msgid "Catut­tha­pā­rāji­kaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth offense entailing expulsion is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc236, ms1V_769
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.13"
msgid "Uddiṭṭhā kho āyasmanto cattāro pārājikā dhammā,"
msgstr "“Venerables, the four rules entailing expulsion have been recited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.14"
msgid "yesaṃ bhikkhu aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā āpajjitvā na labhati bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvāsaṃ,"
msgstr "If a monk commits any one of them, he is no longer part of the community of monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.15"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso."
msgstr "As before, so after, he’s expelled and excluded from the community."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.16"
msgid "Tatthāyasmante pucchāmi—"
msgstr "In regard to this I ask you,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.17"
msgid "“kaccittha parisuddhā”?"
msgstr "‘Are you pure in this?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.18"
msgid "Dutiyampi pucchāmi—"
msgstr "A second time I ask,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.19"
msgid "“kaccittha parisuddhā”?"
msgstr "‘Are you pure in this?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.20"
msgid "Tatiyampi pucchāmi—"
msgstr "A third time I ask,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.21"
msgid "“kaccittha parisuddhā”?"
msgstr "‘Are you pure in this?’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.22"
msgid "Pari­sud­dhet­thā­yasmanto, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "You are pure in this and therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.23"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmīti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.”"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc237, ms1V_770
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.24"
msgid "Pārājikaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The rules entailing expulsion are finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc238, ms1V_771
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.25"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="uddana"><p>
#. REF: sc239, ms1V_772
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.26"
msgid "Methu­nādinnā­dānañca,"
msgstr "Sexual intercourse, and stealing,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.27"
msgid "­manus­sa­vigga­huttari;"
msgstr "Person, super;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.28"
msgid "Pārājikāni cattāri,"
msgstr "The four offenses entailing expulsion—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.29"
msgid "chejjavatthū asaṃsayāti."
msgstr "The foundation is definitively cut off."

#. HTML: </p></div><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc240, ms1V_773
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj4:9.7.30"
msgid "Pārājikakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion is finished."
